section.section:
An elementary school is subject to this subsection if it has a suspension rate that exceeds:
18 percent of its enrollment for the 2005-2006 school year;
16 percent of its enrollment for the 2006-2007 school year;
14 percent of its enrollment for the 2007-2008 school year;
12 percent of its enrollment for the 2008-2009 school year; and
10 percent of its enrollment for the 2009-2010 school year and each school year thereafter.

A school is subject to this subsection if it has a truancy rate that exceeds:
8 percent of its enrollment for the 2008-2009 school year;
6 percent of its enrollment for the 2009-2010 school year;
4 percent of its enrollment for the 2010-2011 school year;
2 percent of its enrollment for the 2011-2012 school year; and
1 percent of its enrollment for the 2012-2013 school year and each school year thereafter.
